The Weeknd was anonymous online for years when he released his first couple of albums because he thought he wasn't good looking enough or the right look to be an artist/singer in the hip hop and r&b world. And look at him now years later he's maintained the same stage name. His first show was sold out and he was accepted through his eclectic sound and musicianship...at least the first few albums lol. Slightly different than tech obviously but I think it also shows that starting off anonish could have benefits to focus and not be so focused on the "image" of whom you are publicly.
